Description: The manufacture and sale of quality automatic feeders.
Full Description: Super-Feed Enterprise, was first established in 1992 with Their first production in 1994. Their only projected specialty (which still is) was the manufacture and sale of quality automatic feeders. They discovered a need for truly dependable feeders, especially for flake food, that could not only be used on a temporary basis (vacations), but could also be installed permanently. Once you use one of Their Super Feeders®, They are confident that you will ultimately use it on a daily basis as many others do. They developed and ultimately patented a very unique mechanical and electronic feeding concept which allowed us to maximize Their investment and efforts into each feeder's mechanical properties, and not into a built-in timer, which could still be operationally restrictive with some applications. Using Their own innovative system, each Super Feeder® offers tremendous flexibility in installation, operation and dependability using just about any external timer or home automation system. As They have done from the very beginning, They will continue to produce Their own Super Feeders® here in the USA to help create and protect Their job market and provide the very best product support Their customers deserve.

Description: PFD offers businesses with website design and development services.
Full Description: The PFD team is currently made up of three people; Oli, Tori and Neil. Collectively they feel they strike a great balance between creativity and technical know-how. They pride ourselves on being friendly, honest and reliable and like to encourage a high level of interaction between their clients and ourselves throughout every project. As they comprise a fairly compact team, it is this personal design experience they feel helps set us apart from their competitors. Oli takes the creative lead on most projects, project manages all work and is heavily involved in all design work. He has over 10 years experience working within the design industry. Tori is primarily a photographer, specialising in food and lifestyle photography here at PFD. The work she has shot has been featured in numerous publications (both print and online) and is used in many of their clients' websites. Sometimes she'll take the creative lead on projects and has a keen design eye, often contributing creatively to much of their work. Neil has extensive development experience in a multitude of languages and forms an integral part of their team, taking their design ideas and bringing them to life. All frontend and backend development is undertaken by Neil. He is extremely meticulous, resulting in clean, efficient code and websites that are crafted with care.

Hemp has an important role to play in creating a better and more sustainable future and for hemp to reach its potential, we advocate for sensible public policy and regulation.
